<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="198" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,562,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,562,587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Black species with legs whitish yellow, except fore trochanter and femur brownish. Head rounded (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,164,599,623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus much shorter than length of epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[718,786,598,623]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[771,786,599,623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); epandrium rather narrower apically, with median row of spine-like setae on inner face (
<figureCitation box="[492,593,634,659]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="198" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,562,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,670,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[353,413,670,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[428,492,670,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish. Rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1418,670,695]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1405,1418,671,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); ocellar triangle with 
<number box="[384,398,707,731]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, close together on face bearing fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number box="[642,684,743,767]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
frontal setulae; 
<number box="[879,893,743,767]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of distinct vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate row of smaller postocular setae. Occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense, short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with yellow setae. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct, short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number box="[683,716,850,875]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number box="[1026,1061,851,875]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1347,1436,850,875]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,230,886,911]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[217,230,887,911]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Short, slightly arched ventrally; dark brown to blackish; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight and scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except one notopleural. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1093,1149,922,947]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1166,1232,922,947]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1219,1232,923,947]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow, except fore trochanter and femur brownish. C 
<number box="[662,672,959,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[701,734,958,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number box="[1115,1125,959,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date box="[1225,1259,959,982]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">7X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number box="[560,570,995,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
about 
<number box="[649,682,995,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C 
<number box="[858,869,995,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
, 3.0– 
<number box="[933,967,994,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.5">3.5</number>
X as long as wide. Femoral formula 
<number box="[1387,1428,994,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">
6– 
<date box="[1415,1428,994,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1915-07-14" valueMax="1915-07-15" valueMin="1915-07-14">7</date>
</number>
/ 
<number box="[151,220,1030,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
/ 
<number box="[230,300,1030,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16</number>
/ 
<number box="[310,351,1030,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
; denticles confined to distal 
<number box="[675,713,1030,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="0.6">0.6</number>
, becoming closer together distally, black, 
<number box="[1189,1203,1031,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, without distal discontinuity, converging at apex. T 
<number box="[631,641,1067,1091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[673,708,1066,1091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="0.6">0.6</number>
X as long as F 
<number box="[879,890,1067,1091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; about 
<number box="[226,282,1103,1127]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short, pale setulae, denser distally; without apicoventral extension on T 
<number box="[664,674,1139,1163]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
but with strong, black subapical spine. Mid- and hind legs slender with fine setae; T 
<number box="[357,369,1175,1199]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[881,946,1174,1199]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[964,1036,1174,1199]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1020,1036,1175,1199]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Membrane slightly yellow, veins yellowish; R 
<number box="[293,301,1225,1239]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[310,317,1225,1239]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
long and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number box="[1106,1190,1210,1235]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="0.6499999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.7</number>
distance between end of R 
<number box="[203,211,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[291,299,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[308,315,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="5.0">5</number>
; R 
<number box="[352,360,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[369,376,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="5.0">5</number>
fork acute (~ 
<number box="[549,581,1249,1274]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="60.0">60</number>
°), distal to position of M 
<number box="[878,883,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[894,903,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by shorter than length of R 
<number box="[1289,1297,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[1334,1342,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[1428,1436,1264,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
convergent distally; R 
<number box="[397,405,1303,1317]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 
<number box="[434,469,1288,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X as long as R 
<number box="[632,640,1303,1317]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending at level of R 
<number box="[1087,1095,1303,1317]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~ 
<date box="[1123,1158,1288,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<number box="[1123,1137,1288,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[337,453,1327,1352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites and sternites brownish; tergite 
<number box="[932,946,1327,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="8.0">8</number>
shorter than sternite 
<number box="[1198,1214,1327,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1231,1362,1327,1352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black. Cercus very short (
<figureCitation box="[542,609,1363,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[594,609,1363,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), not reaching half length of epandrium, wide basally and pointed at apex, left and right cerci closely approximated dorsally, distinctly setose. Epandrium wide, rounded at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1350,1421,1399,1424]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1406,1421,1399,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), distinct strong setae on outer face; median row of stronger setae on inner face (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1126,1435,1460]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
); articulated to hypandrium by weak point anteriorly. Surstylus absent. Hypandrium inflated, rather rounded, with strong setae; gonocoxal apodeme projecting as narrow process just beyond anterior margin of hypandrium. Subepandrial sclerite with short triangular anterior projection; 
<number box="[502,516,1543,1567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
posterior fine and long finger-like processes with long setae at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1349,1423,1543,1568]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1406,1423,1543,1567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus strongly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[475,543,1579,1604]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[527,543,1579,1604]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
), extending well beyond hypandrium apex, bluntly pointed apically, with apical membranous area, covered with spicules and 
<number box="[669,683,1615,1639]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
dorsal hook-like processes apically (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1175,1615,1640]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1159,1175,1615,1639]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[236,433,1651,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Specimen length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[448,537,1651,1675]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[548,688,1651,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">wing length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[702,791,1651,1675]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[802,889,1651,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
