<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,562,2036]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1975,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[324,642,1975,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicercata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,642,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Hemerodromia brevicercata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[651,743,1975,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[651,743,1975,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
appears to belong to the informal 
<emphasis box="[1145,1271,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">empiformis</emphasis>
species group proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="MacDonald" box="[295,511,2011,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" refString="MacDonald, J. F. (1998) Review of the genus Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae: Hemerodromiinae) of America north of Mexico. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 100, 792 - 823." type="journal article" year="1998">
MacDonald (
<number box="[443,503,2011,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, on the basis of the short cercus, but differs from other species of this group by having a rounded head and different shaped epandrium. 
<taxonomicName box="[818,1139,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicercata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[818,1139,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Hemerodromia brevicercata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1150,1244,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1150,1244,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Melander" authorityName="Melander" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coleophora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">H. coleophora</emphasis>
Melander
</taxonomicName>
in sharing a similar shaped cercus (
<figureCitation box="[852,940,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[221,1379,196,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[195,1391,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Hemerodromia carioca sp. nov., holotype ♂. 8., habitus, lateral view; 9, wing; 10, terminalia, lateral view; 11, terminalia, dorsal view; 12, subepandrial sclerite, epandrium and surstylus, dorsal view; 13, phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 14, terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233674/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
Fig. 
<number box="[912,940,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
vs. fig. 
<quantity box="[1053,1117,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" unit="in" value="17.0">17 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="MacDonald" box="[1131,1345,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="MacDonald, J. F. (1998) Review of the genus Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae: Hemerodromiinae) of America north of Mexico. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 100, 792 - 823." type="journal article" year="1998">
MacDonald, 
<number box="[1285,1345,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicercata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">H. brevicercata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[298,388,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[298,388,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the head is rounded (
<figureCitation box="[633,699,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
Fig. 
<number box="[686,699,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), fore trochanter and femur are brownish (
<figureCitation box="[1184,1249,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
Fig. 
<number box="[1237,1249,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) and epandrium rather narrower apically, with median row of stronger setae on inner face (
<figureCitation box="[990,1092,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName box="[1145,1308,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coleophora">
<emphasis box="[1145,1308,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">H. coleophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the head is flattened dorsoventrally, legs yellowish and epandrium slender and straight basally, and then abruptly enlarged at or slightly beyond the distal third (
<bibRefCitation author="MacDonald" box="[508,802,332,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="MacDonald, J. F. (1998) Review of the genus Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae: Hemerodromiinae) of America north of Mexico. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 100, 792 - 823." type="journal article" year="1998">
MacDonald, 
<number box="[656,715,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1998.0">1998</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[771,802,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="17.0">17</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
